title: Wisconsin Disability Vote Coalition

sponsor.name: REV UP, American Association of People with Disabilities (AAPD)

description:
The Wisconsin Disability Vote Coalition (WDVC) is a non-partisan effort to help ensure full participation in the entire electoral process of voters with disabilities, including registering to vote, casting a vote, and accessing polling places.

The Coalition is on the frontline providing training and support to voters with disabilities, family members, and service providers. While much progress has been made in improving the accessibility of our elections, many opportunities for improvement remain.

Disability Vote Coalition Goals
Educate the disability community about voting rights and access issues.
Increase voter turnout among people with disabilities and their allies.
Work with elected officials and other policy makers to advance policies and practices that support accessible elections.
Encourage organizations to conduct local get-out-the-vote drives and outreach.

Disability Vote Coalition Leadership
The Coalition is coordinated by Disability Rights Wisconsin (DRW) and Wisconsin Board for People with Developmental Disabilities (BPDD). It includes over 40 community agency partners as well as self-advocates and other community members.
View a list of Coalition leadership and community agency partners (accessible PDF).

title: Virtual Book Club: "Attack From Within"

sponsor.name: Building Bridges for America Action Fund

description:
# *Attack From Within* by Barbara McQuade

Join progressive grassroots organizers from across the county in reading & discussing *Attack From Within* by Barbara McQuade. Misinformation is a key issue plaguing our democracy. Join us to discuss how it happens, how it impacts communities and what we can do about it.

## FAQ:

### 1. How can I order the book?

Support a local bookstore by [**clicking here**](https://bookshop.org/p/books/attack-from-within-how-disinformation-is-sabotaging-democracy-and-the-rule-of-law-barbara-mcquade/20068804). Purchasing or ownership of the book is not required to attend. Also consider checking your local library (click **[here](https://libraryfinder.org/)** to find a library near you). 

### 2. What is the reading schedule?

For this book, we will have a 5 week session. Reading is not required to attend, but we highly encourage it. A Reading/Discussion Guide will be sent prior to our meet-up to compliment your journey & our discussion.

**WEEK 1 - APR 21:**

* Introduction: Disinformed to Death
* CH1: The Authoritarian Playbook: How Disinformers Gain Power


**WEEK 2 - APR 28:**

* CH2: From Gaslighting to Liar’s Dividend: Disinformation Tactics
* CH3: Hearts Are Bigger Than Minds: Why Disinformation Works

**WEEK 3 - MAY 05:**

* CH4: The New Engines of Disinformation: The Danger of Emerging Technology
* CH5: The Land of the Free: Why America is Particularly Vulnerable to Disinformation

**WEEK 4 - MAY 12:**

* CH6: “Stop the Steal”: Disinformation is Destroying Democracy
* CH7: “Somebody Is Going to Get Killed”: Disinformation Is Endangering Public Safety and National Security
* CH8: Trial By Combat: Disinformation Is Eroding the Rule of Law

**WEEK 5 - MAY 19:**

* CH9: We Alone Can Fix It: Proposed Solutions
* CH10: We Hold These Truths to Be Self-Evident: A Way Forward


### 3. Will there be any special guest?

TBD, stay tuned.

### 4. How do I join the virtual event? 

We use the Zoom platform & individuals who sign up, will be sent the Zoom link via Mobilize. For information on joining a Zoom meeting, [**click here**](https://support.zoom.us/hc/en-us/articles/201362193-Joining-a-Zoom-meeting). Please note that our meet-ups will be recorded for promotional purposes.

### 5. Who is Building Bridges for America?

We are an all-volunteer, nationwide group that mobilizes and empowers networks of relational grassroots organizers to support campaigns and causes based in progressive values. Learn more about us on our [**website**](www.buildingbridgesforamerica.com) & give us a follow on [**Facebook**](https://www.facebook.com/groups/buildingbridges4america), [**Instagram**](https://www.instagram.com/buildbridges4am/), [**Threads**](https://www.threads.net/@buildbridges4am), [**Twitter/X**](https://twitter.com/buildbridges4am) & [**YouTube**](https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCF2XFBp48fNJjc7n2N4WxZA).

description:
**Join the Rise for Freedom Coalition for a series of live online trainings intended for in-person groups nationwide for 6-8 weeks.** The goal of the training series is to bring people together, grow & strengthen their local networks, and get ready to mobilize to demand democracy in this new challenging environment.

*   Training content will be presented live and breakouts will take place in-person in people’s living rooms and other activist organized spaces. 
    
*   Follow up asks deemed the most important to the moment will be shared at the end of trainings as appropriate.
    
*   Training is a flexible tool that can help build for specific events as well as build existing and new local groups of people who can take action together.
    

#### **Why Trainings?**

Trainings are critical for our movement because they:

*   **Engage and recruit** more people into the freedom and democracy movement
    
*   **Educate** and onboard new activists
    
*   **Energize** large numbers of people for mobilizing and create space for local organizing and planning
    
*   **Elevate:** train higher skill activists and new and younger movement  leadership
    

**Who is Rise for Democracy For?**

This training is for people who love our country and understand the threat of autocracy before us, and want to do something about it. If you're moderate politically - this is your place! You are welcome and important here. If you're a pro-democracy conservative - this is your place! You are welcome and important in these trainings. If you’re progressive, this training is for you. 

#### **All Trainings Will Include:**

*   Music
    
*   An icebreaker
    
*   Asks for local leaders to help you prepare for action
    
*   Outreach mini training and goal setting (e.g. text 5 ppl and get 1 commit to come to your next meeting, recruit one neighbor to attend etc)
    
*   One digital hygiene tip 
    
*   One core 1.5- 2 hour training module
    
*   Breakouts for in-person and online for folks who are alone, to plan and participate in activities
    

Training calls will _not_ include lengthy one way communications about the ongoing attacks on democracy and communities. That’s a space other orgs and collaboratives we believe can and will fill.

#### **Rise for Freedom Training Timeline:**

*   **Thurs. March 27 – First In-Person Meetings & Onboarding for New Folks:** Program Orientation & Context Setting, Outreach & Digital Hygiene
    
*   **Thurs. April 3 –** How did we get here? Intro to organizing under creeping autocracy
    
*   **Thurs. April 10 –** Building to a critical mass locally (outreach)
    
*   **Thurs. April 17 –** How to Talk to People You Might Disagree With
    
*   **Thurs. April 24 –** Harnessing Our Power to End Political Violence and Repression
    
*   **Thurs. May 1 – BREAK (no training): Find or host a May Day mobilization:** [**may1dayofaction.org**](https://www.may1dayofaction.org/) **(immigration focused) or** [**maydaystrong.org**](https://maydaystrong.org/) **(union led)**
    
*   **Thurs. May 8 –** De-escalation & Advanced Strategic organizing skills
    
*   **Thurs. May 15 –** Mutual Aid & Structures for Stronger Local Organizing
    
*   **Thurs. May 22 –** Advanced Organizing Skills: Choosing your Tactics 
    
*   **Thurs. May 29** **–** Digital Hygiene for Activists
    
*   **Thurs. June 5** **–** Media Storytelling with a Focus on Broadcast and Social Media
    

_\*May wish to do trainings en masse in-person, repeat training series and/or move focus more to mobilizing._
    

**Partners include:** 

_Public Citizen, Women’s March, League of Women Voters US, Declaration for American Democracy Coalition, Center for Common Ground, Clean Elections Minnesota, Corporate Accountability, Generation Common Good, Lift Our Vote, No Voice Unheard, Peace Action, Unitarian Universalists for Social Justice, AFGE Local 704, DC Peace Team, Fourth Branch Action, Indivisible Hill Country, Indivisible Portola Valley, Media and Democracy Project, Citizen Action/Illinois, Peace, Justice, Sustainability NOW!, People For the American Way, Speaking the Key of WE/Charlotte Clergy Coalition for Justice, Task Force for Democracy, Texans Against Gerrymandering, This Land, The Workers Circle, #ResistTrump Campaign, Our Revolution_

Ann Telnaes is a Pulitzer-winning editorial cartoonist and vocal advocate for press freedom. We will discuss with her the role and power of editorial cartoonists in democracies - and how we can support and better appreciate their work. 

Infamously, in 2025 her draft editorial cartoon was rejected outright by Washington Post opinion editor and fellow Jeff Bezos employee David Shipley. 

The cartoon featured Jeff Bezos (Amazon/Whole Foods/Zappos/Twitch/Ring/Audible), Sam Altman (OpenAI), Mark Zuckerberg (Meta/Facebook/Instagram/Threads/WhatsApp), Patrick Soon-Shiong (Los Angeles Times), and Mickey Mouse (employee of Disney-ABC).

Read more here:

https://mediaanddemocracyproject.substack.com/p/ann-telnaes-the-media-and-democracy

Sign up for her blog “Open Windows”  to access and receive her powerful editorial cartoons to your INBOX https://anntelnaes.substack.com 

Learn more about her and her body of work at https://anntelnaes.com

“As an editorial cartoonist, my job is to hold powerful people and institutions accountable. For the first time, my editor prevented me from doing that critical job. So I have decided to leave the Post. I doubt my decision will cause much of a stir and that it will be dismissed because I’m just a cartoonist. But I will not stop holding truth to power through my cartooning, because as they say, “Democracy dies in darkness”. 
- Ann Telnaes.

For May, the club will be discussing Toni Morrison's first novel, The Bluest Eye, published in 1970.  The book vividly captures the anguish of a child's desire being fulfilled and the fear and loneliness that lie at its core. The book begins in the fall of 1941; America is still getting over the Great Depression and has not yet joined the Second World War. The book's story centers around the Breedlove family, and their two kids are named Sammy and Pecola. Pecola is the one who wishes she had blue eyes and wonders if her life would be less unpleasant if she could change their color and, by extension, how they look.

description:
Join the National Democratic Training Committee on Tuesday, May 13th from 1:00 - 2:00 pm ET for our free virtual live training: **Tech Time: Building a List in VoteBuilder.**

  

This session is designed to teach you the technical skills needed to effectively use VoteBuilder for list-building. Unlike our other virtual live trainings, this session focuses more on demonstrating hands-on, hard skills rather than high-level theory and strategy. If you already have access VoteBuilder, there will be opportunities to follow along and practice throughout the session.

  

We’re here to help, so join us to learn the following:

*   Discuss the purpose and benefits of using VoteBuilder for list-building
*   Evaluate the filtering options available in VoteBuilder and their strategic applications
*   Demonstrate how to create a targeted persuasion list

  

_Have accessibility questions? Reply to your registration email to confirm your requirements or request more information._

title: Weekday Canvassing for CM Crystal Hudson
description:
With just a few short months until the June Primary Election, we need all hands on deck to help get Crystal re-elected to the City Council! title: Defend Democracy — Chippewa Falls
description:
Join Chippewa Valley Indivisible, Chippewa Falls Democratic Party, and other citizen groups to expand the Defend Democracy to Chippewa Falls! Come to the Peace Circle with your signs to let everyone know we are standing up for Chippewa Falls! Let's get the movement growing in the north!

Take action now to Defend Democracy! Take a stand against Trump, this administration, and DOGE for their unlawful and unconstitutional actions. Take a stand for protecting Social Security, Medicaid, federal agencies, national parks, due process, rule of law, the environment, and more. Defend our democracy for our families, friends, and neighbors. Get your signs ready and come let the community know this matters to you!

There's no such thing as bad weather, just bad clothing choices! Dress for Rally Success! Let's gather together and speak up for our children, grandchildren, and our community!

Two public parking lots on Bridge and River.
